sentences: The group is based in Katsushika, Tokyo, and was formed in 2010 by eight classmates of the same junior high school.
Fischer's have gained popularity especially in the younger generations becoming the most-viewed YouTube channel in Japan in 2019.
Fischer's was formed on February 25, 2010.
In October 2015, Daibū left the group stating that he "was unreliable as a friend" and "broke a rule within the members", leaving the group with seven members.
On April 27, 2018, the group made their first appearance on TV Asahi's music program Music Station performing their song Niji.
Since 2018, the group has participated in Momoiro Uta Gassen on New Year's Eve, airing on BS Nippon Television, Fuji TV NEXT, Nippon Broadcasting System, etc.
In 2019, Fischer's collaborated with the One Piece series in a manga spin-off series
On September 16, 2019, Fischer's set the Guinness world record for the largest game of tag with 10,908 participants at Expo Commemoration Park in Suita, Osaka Prefecture.

On January 11, 2021, Fischer's posted their third 100-minute tag video.
As of May 2021, Fischer's was the most-viewed YouTube channel in Japan with 14.4 billion views, and the 7th most-subscribed channel in Japan with 6.94 million subcribers.
